{
  "texts": [
    "The wording of the person-specific instructions were modified slightly from Study 1 to (a) explicitly define the theories to be described and (b) only indirectly classify the theories as \"conspiracies\".",
    "The first question's wording was:",
    "\"Throughout history, various theories have emerged that suggest certain significant events or situations are the result of secret plans by individuals or groups.",
    "These theories often offer alternative explanations for events than those that are widely accepted by the public or presented by official sources.",
    "Some people call these 'conspiracy theories'."
  ]
}